Oh, nature! How divine thy art,
In hues of green and blue thou'rt painted,
Thy beauty doth impart
A sense of calmness to our hearts,
As we stand here in awe, enchanted.

The trees that sway, o'er mountains high,
Their leaves dance in the gentle breeze,
While birds sing by and low,
In harmony with all they see.

The sky so vast above our heads,
A canvas painted with such grace,
A palette of reds and purples spread,
As if God himself took up a brush to trace.

Oh, nature! Thy secrets we'll unveil,
For in thy depths, our souls find peace,
The scent of flowers that wafts down trail,
A fragrance that no words can release.

Thy rivers flow, with such delight,
Reflecting skies above their course,
While fish swim freely through the night,
In waters clear and pure as crystal source.

Nature, you are a sight to behold,
A wonder that we cannot fathom,
From sunrise to sunset, your tale is told,
And in our hearts, forever romantic.
